                        <div class="blog-text">


                            <h4>Amazon's 16 Leadership Principles</h4>
                            
                            <div class="left-about">
                                <ol>
                                    <li> <strong>Customer Obsession</strong>: Leaders start with the customer and work backward. They strive to earn and keep customer trust.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Ownership</strong>: Leaders act on behalf of the entire company and never say, "That’s not my job."</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Invent and Simplify</strong>: Leaders innovate and simplify, being open to new ideas and doing more with less.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Are Right, A Lot</strong>: Leaders have strong judgment, seek diverse perspectives, and work to disconfirm their beliefs.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Learn and Be Curious</strong>: Leaders continuously learn and are curious about new possibilities.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Hire and Develop the Best</strong>: Leaders raise the bar with every hire and promotion, recognizing exceptional talent.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Insist on the Highest Standards</strong>: Leaders drive high-quality outputs and ensure defects are fixed.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Think Big</strong>: Leaders inspire results by thinking boldly and creating ambitious goals.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Bias for Action</strong>: Leaders value speed in decision-making, acknowledging that many actions are reversible.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Frugality</strong>: Leaders accomplish more with less, fostering resourcefulness and self-sufficiency.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Earn Trust</strong>: Leaders listen attentively, speak candidly, and treat others respectfully.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Dive Deep</strong>: Leaders stay connected to details, audit frequently, and question inconsistencies.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Have Backbone; Disagree and Commit</strong>: Leaders respectfully challenge decisions but commit wholly once determined.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Deliver Results</strong>: Leaders focus on key inputs and deliver quality results on time.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Strive to Be Earth’s Best Employer</strong>: Leaders create an inclusive, productive, and fun work environment.</li>
                                    <li> <strong>Success and Scale Bring Broad Responsibility</strong>: Leaders act responsibly to improve the world for future generations.</li>
                                </ol>
    
                            </div>  

